<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--DogPlunge     08-24 0166</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Dog Plunge,0173</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dog Survives 12-Floor Fall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MYRTLE BEACH, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 3-pound Yorkshire terrier survived a
fall from a 12th-floor balcony and may be walking again by the end
of the week, a veterinarian says.
   ``It's really a lucky dog,'' said veterinarian Earl Johnson, who
treated the tan and black dog named Missy. ``I didn't think she was
going to make it, to tell you the truth ... it's a definite
miracle.''
   Doctors said Monday the dog had an 85 percent to 90 percent
chance of total recovery.
   Missy fell Friday from the penthouse balcony of the Sea Mark
Tower condominium.
   Her owners, Roy and Ann Gipson, said strong winds created a
vacuum that sucked the small dog through a 5-inch-wide opening in a
guard rail.
   Missy landed in a sandy area, just missing a brick walkway and
an air conditioner. A tree limb apparently helped break her fall.
   Missy was in shock with a broken leg when taken to an animal
hospital.
</TEXT>
