<1ST_LINE>r a PM-NYCSchools-Glance     08-24 0107</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-NYC Schools-Glance,0117</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>A Statistical Look at NYC Schools</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-NYC School Chief</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Just how big is the nation's biggest school
system?
   Here, at a glance, is a statistical profile:
   _ 1988-89 budget _ $5.6 billion.
   _ Number of schools _ 974.
   _ Number of teachers _ 61,991.
   _ Central administrative staff _ 6,447.
   _ Number of students _ 940,000.
   _ Number of handicapped students _ 113,000.
   _ Ethnic composition of student body: 38.1 percent black, 33.9
percent Hispanic, 21.3 percent white, 6.6 percent Asian@Pacific,
0.1 percent Native American@Eskimo.
   _ Estimated high school dropout rate _ 29.2 percent.
</TEXT>
