<HEAD>Danish Princes In Auto Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LUZECH, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Crown Prince Frederik of Denmark was
slightly injured in an automobile accident near the chateau of his
father, the Count of Monpezat, a family spokeswoman said today.
   Prince Frederik, 20, was treated for slight injuries to his head
and shoulder and was released from the hospital, said Dina
Luttichau, the family's private secretary. His brother Joachim, 19,
who was driving, was not injured, she said.
   Their French-made Peugeot 205 swerved to avoid another car and
overturned twice on Tuesday night on the road from the town of
Luzech to nearby Cahors in mountainous south-central France.
   Also in the car were two friends, Peter Heering and Anders
Mostke Leth, who was treated for rib injuries.
