Monday that the panel found that Monroe had been deprived of his
rights. During the hearing, Monroe maintained his innocence.
   Prosecutors contend that Lenora Collins, 33, was killed after
she told Monroe he was being evicted from an apartment in the
family's duplex. The victim's daughter, then 11, also was stabbed
and identified Monroe as the assailant.
   Eighteen inmates, including three this year, have been executed
in Louisiana's electric chair since the U.S. Supreme Court
reinstated the death penalty in 1976.
