<1ST_LINE>r a AM-SwimsuitRapist     08-24 0205</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Swimsuit Rapist,0209</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Suspect Belived Responsible for 22 Assaults in 11 Cities</HEAD>
<DATELINE>IRVING, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities in the Dallas-Fort Worth area
have joined forces to search for a man believed to have sexually
assaulted at least 22 women at apartment complex swimming pools
since May.
   Police officers in 11 communities said the man targets lone
women at pools, shows them a small semiautomatic handgun and orders
them to remove their swimsuits and to perform sexual acts. The
suspect then usually orders victims to run away while he steals the
swimsuits.
   Police Lt. K.L. Roe said authorities will have their third joint
meeting this week.
   Farmers Branch Dectective Dave Lemons described the man as
active and persistent. He said when the man has been unsuccessful
in assaulting one woman, he has approached as many as three others
in different cities in as many hours.
   Officials said the joint investigation has tracked details of
the suspect's movements.
   ``The guy is most active on Mondays and Wednesdays, and between
the hours of noon to about 4 p.m., but he has varied the days and
hours on a few occasions,'' Lemons said. ``Besides having an
outdoor fetish, he likes knowing that the police are close behind
him.''
