<HEAD>Few Ask College To Pay Back Donations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NORTON, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Few donors to Wheaton College have cashed
in on the offer by New England's oldest women's college to refund
$16 million in donations to anyone unhappy about its decision to
admit men.
   As of Wednesday, 54 donors had been refunded $126,000, said Lisa
Byrnes, a Wheaton spokeswoman.
   The 54 include six who went to court claiming they had been
deceived into donating to a 150th anniversary fund-raising campaign
by a college they thought would remain women-only.
