Wheaton agreed to refund $120,000 to the donors who went to court
and to write to 3,800 other donors offering to return donation. The
offer expires Aug. 31.
   The liberal arts college founded in 1834 has about 1,100
students. In September it will admit 74 men in a 407-member
first-year class.
