<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A government inquiry into a train crash
in southern India that killed 105 people and injured 200 others
blamed railroad workers for the accident, it was reported Wednesday
   Nine of the 14 passenger cars on the Island Express derailed
July 8.
