<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--BridgeInspections     08-24 0094</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Bridge Inspections,90</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rule to Tighten Bridge Inspections Announced</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A new rule to tighten state inspections of
bridges was announced Wednesday by the Federal Highway
Administration.
   It will require states to list and keep records of bridges with
certain failure-causing features and those that require underwater
and other special inspections.
   But the rule also allows certain bridges to be inspected at
intervals longer than the two years now required. Those include
bridges that are relatively new, are in good condition, are in low
traffic areas and have proven performance histories.
</TEXT>
