<HEAD>Democratic Donkeys Up For Adoption</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: `K' is cq in 4th graf</NOTE>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Some special Democrats who showed up during last
month's Democratic National Convention are looking for a place to
stretch their legs _ all four of them.
   They're the donkeys brought to Georgia's Stone Mountain Park for
the festivities surrounding the party gathering.
   The park plans to keep two of the animals, but is searching for
homes for the rest. They're available for $150 each.
   ``These donkeys are not just no-name personalities,'' said K
Thweatt, public relations manager for the park. ``Neither Dukakis
nor Bentsen has been claimed. I think Jesse Jackson's still there
and I think Grits and Fritz are still there too.
   ``They probably went to more prestigious parties and events than
any of us, so we feel like they're very well-traveled donkeys,''
she said.
   Thweatt said she wasn't told she'd be an agent for donkeys when
she took her job, but it could be worse.
   ``I shudder to think what would've happened to the park if we
had had the Republican Convention,'' she said. ``I can't imagine
all those elephants.''
