<HEAD>Defense Ministry Reports Contra Attacks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAGUA, Nicaragua (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Defense Ministry reported
Wednesday that Nicaraguan rebels killed three civilians, kidnapped
10 people and wounded two others in separate attacks in recent days.
   A Ministry statement also said 15 of the U.S.-backed rebels,
known as Contras, were killed in ``combat actions in response to
attacks by the counter-revolutionaries on our troops.''
   The leftist Sandinista government and rebels agreed to a truce
in March, but the two sides failed to reach a permanent settlement
in the 7-year-old civil war. Negotiations broke off June 9, and
each side has charged the other with violating the truce.
   The Defense Ministry statement reported six Contra attacks
against government forces between Thursday and Sunday with five
attacks against civilians.
   The statement did not say if any of the casualties included
government troops.
