   Here is a complete list of nominees in
all categories for the 40th Annual Prime Time Emmy Awards to be
presented Saturday and Sunday nights by the Television Academy of
Arts & Sciences.
   1. COMEDY SERIES: ``Cheers,'' NBC; ``Frank's Place,'' CBS; ``The
Golden Girls,'' NBC; ``Night Court,'' NBC; ``The Wonder Years,''
ABC.
   2. DRAMA SERIES: ``Beauty and the Beast,'' CBS; ``L.A. Law,''
NBC; ``Rumpole of the Bailey _ Mystery!,'' PBS; ``St. Elsewhere,''
NBC; ``thirtysomething,'' ABC.
   3. MINISERIES: ``Baby M,'' ABC; ``Billionaire Boys Club,'' NBC;
``Gore Vidal's Lincoln,'' NBC; ``The Murder of Mary Phagan,'' NBC.
   4. VARIETY, MUSIC OR COMEDY PROGRAM: ``Irving Berlin's 100th
Birthday Celebration,'' CBS; ``Late Night with David Letterman,''
NBC; ``Late Night with David Letterman 6th Anniversary Special,''
NBC; ``The Smother's Brothers Comedy Hour,'' CBS; ``The Tracey
Ullman Show,'' FBC.
   5. DRAMA@COMEDY SPECIAL: ``The Ann Jillian Story,'' NBC; ``The
Attic: The Hiding of Anne Frank: General Foods Golden Showcase,''
CBS; ``Foxfire: Hallmark Hall of Fame,'' CBS; ``Inherit the Wind,''
NBC; ``The Taking of Flight 847: The Uli Derickson Story,'' NBC.
   6. CLASSICAL PROGRAM IN THE PERFORMING ARTS: ``All That Bach,''
PBS; ``American Ballet Theater's Romeo and Juliet, Live From
Lincoln Center: Great Performances,'' PBS; ``Dance in America:
Balanchine and Cunningham _ An Evening at American Ballet Theater,
Great Performances,'' PBS; ``New York Philharmonic: New Year's Eve
Celebration with Zubin Mehta and Kathleen Battle, Live From Lincoln
Center,'' PBS; ``Nixon in China: Great Performances,'' PBS.
   7. INFORMATIONAL SERIES: ``The Barbara Walters Specials,'' ABC;
``Buster Keaton: A Hard Act to Follow, American Masters,'' PBS;
``Entertainment Tonight,'' SYN; ``Nature,'' PBS; ``Siskel and
Ebert,'' SYN.
   8. INFORMATIONAL SPECIAL: ``Bacall on Bogart: Great
Performances,'' PBS; ``Dear America: Letters Home from Vietnam,''
HBO; ``Directed By William Walter: American Masters,'' PBS;
``George Gershwin Remembered,'' PBS; ``Legacy of the Hollywood
Blacklist,'' PBS.
   9. ANIMATED PROGRAM: ``Brave Little Toaster,'' DIS; ``A
Claymation Christmas Celebration,'' CBS; ``A Garfield Christmas
Special,'' CBS.
   10. CHILDREN'S PROGRAM: ``Jim Henson's A Muppet Family
