<TEXT>
   One of the West Coast's largest shipbuilding and
tugboat companies emerged from federal bankruptcy protection when
family ownership was transferred to employees.
   Unimar International Inc., formerly WFI Industries, began
operations with its 400 employees holding 73 percent of the
company's stock Tuesday under a reorganization orchestrated by the
investment banking firm Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc.
