<TEXT>
   Public approval of labor unions has climbed by
six percentage points since 1981 while disapproval of them has
declined by 10 percent, according to a Gallup Organization poll.
   The poll, conducted in June, showed 61 percent of the public at
large approved of unions while 25 percent disapproved and 14
percent had no opinion.
</TEXT>
