   The market has been trending lower all month in sluggish trading.
   Investors have generally shown little inclination to buy stocks
because they are fearful that the recent pace of economic expansion
is strong enough that inflation is likely to pick up.
   On Tuesday, the government reported that consumer prices were up
modestly in July while orders for durable goods tumbled.
   But while the reports sparked a mild rally in bond prices,
stocks failed to follow through.
   Nonetheless, some analysts feel a mild rebound may be coming
because stocks have fallen so far in the past few weeks.
