<TEXT>
   Stock prices managed to creep into positive
territory Wednesday, as a strong start on Wall Street pulled London
equities higher.
   However, dealers said activity remained sparse, as many
investors stayed on the sidelines ahead of Thursday's release of
British trade figures for July and the upcoming three-day holiday
weekend in Britain.
