<1ST_LINE>d f AM-MicrowaveExports     08-24 0115</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Microwave Exports,0120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Sharp To Export 100,000 Microwave Ovens From Tennessee</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sharp Electronics Corp. said Wednesday it plans
to export 100,000 Tennessee-made microwave ovens to Europe by the
end of 1989.
   The U.S. subsidiary of Japan's Sharp Corp. said the ovens, made
in Memphis, Tenn., will be shipped to 11 European countries: West
Germany, the Netherlands, Switzerland, Belgium, France, Austria,
Italy, Spain, Greece, Portugal and Britain.
   The Memphis plant, Sharp's only U.S. factory, produces about
90,000 color televisions and 65,000 microwave ovens a month. In
addition, it began making personal computers in January.
   The company said it is studying the possible export of other
American-made products to Europe and Asia.
</TEXT>
